Second Department,

February, 1974

(February 4, 1974)* In the Matter of David Hool, Jr., Petitioner, v. Harold E. Collins, Judge of the County Court, Nassau County, et al., Respondents.

Not printed with other decisions of February 4, 1974, 43 A D 2d 938 [Rep.--

Proceeding, pursuant to 78 of the CPLR to prohibit the respondents from barring *657a certain portion of the general public from a criminal trial now in progress, wherein petitioner is the defendant. Application denied, and proceeding dismissed, on the merits, without costs. Shapiro, Acting P. J., Cohalan, Christ and Munder, JJ., concur.
